benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to bundle

covered: Valid Request: Numerous TC01, TC02, TC03 cover successful updates with valid payloads and required headers.
Non-Existing Resource: TC05 covers 404 for missing bundle.
Authorization: TC06 (missing header), TC10 (unauthorized) and related header usage across tests.

Validation and error handling: TC07 (malformed JSON), TC08 (missing body), TC09 (extra/unsupported fields), TC12 (SQL injection attempt), TC11 (503 service unavailable via dependency/service), TC20 (integration/data inconsistency leading to 500).
Edge cases: TC13-15 for max fields, max value length, and empty value; TC16 for unexpected URL parameters; TC22-24 state variations; TC25 backward compatibility.
State variation: TC22 (no existing fields), TC23 (update existing fields), TC24 partial update scenario.
gaps: Concurrency control: No explicit tests for race conditions when multiple users update the same bundle simultaneously.
Rate limiting: No tests for throttling or handling high request rate.
Caching behavior: No tests validating ETag/Cache-Control or other caching headers.
Partial update rejection: No test showing partial updates are disallowed if not permitted (though TC24 implies partial updates are allowed; a negative test would clarify policy).
Pagination: Not applicable for PUT payload but guideline mentions pagination for large datasets in GET context; no PUT pagination tests are present (not strictly necessary here).
recommendations: Add a negative test for partial updates being rejected when not allowed to clarify partial update policy.
Introduce concurrency/race-condition tests to ensure updates are atomic and consistent when multiple clients update the same bundle simultaneously.
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to ensure the API handles bursts gracefully.
Add caching behavior tests (ETag/Cache-Control) to validate client-side caching semantics and server-side optimizations.
Include explicit tests for repeated identical updates to verify idempotency where applicable.
